<Author>Dupont16450
<Content>Great hotel We had a long weekend in Barcelona before moving on to the Costa Brava for 2 weeks. We wanted to experience the culture and life of the city and wanted to stay in a good hotel. We were not disappointed. The Villa Emilia was everything we could have asked for - and we are quite fussy people! The hotel was smart and very modern and but was comfortable with a welcoming feel. Our room overlooked the intersection of two streets and had a ceiling to floor glass wall which made the views out spectacular. I could have spent hours simply watching the comings and goings of the locals throughout the day. The room was well equipped and of a reasonable size. The staff were friendly and helpful and we felt well looked after. The breakfasts were good and we had lunch there on one occasion which was very enjoyable. We are both vegetarians and we were well catered for, although I can't remember whether or not there were vegetarian meals provided in the evenings. We ate out each evening as we wanted to experience the city and it was a relatively short walk to the centre. We will certainly not look for another hotel on our next visit to Barcelona. 
