<Author>espruytte
<Content>Loved the open air lounge terrace bar on the rooftop !! Great design hotel next to a metro station which makes it very convenient to move around in Barcelona.It is located in a quite street with little noise, which is a plus.One of the great features of this new hotel is the superb open air lounge terrace bar on the rooftop which allows one to chill out after a long day in the city. Also the Zinc bar at ground level is very nice for a nice bottle of Cava!Great buffet breakfast with a large variety of breads, marmalade, eggs, ham, cheese, yogurt, cereals,... and you can order an espresso or cappuccino without supplement.Two negative comments:1. No A/C available in the Fall and Winter because the system switches automatically to heating as soon as the outside temperature is below a certain level. This is very annoying because it is always too hot in hotel rooms. I am not the first one to mention this on Tripadvisor.2. The bed mattresses are extremely hard and it is very tough for back and shoulders. The owner of the hotel is German and the employees told us HE liked it this way, but we did not!3. They omitted to make up our room the first day. They told us the cleaning team was gone and that they could not do anything about it before the next morning.I would recommend it (when the A/C is ON and with softer bed mattresses!) 
