<Author>Bristlehound
<Content>What a great Hotel! My wife and I have just returned from a four night break at this wonderful Hotel.The staff were all very friendly. The bar staff especially couldn't do enough.The Hotel is very modern and contemporary. It is very very clean. The corridors and all the public areas being as clean as your room!The patisserie next door but one to the Hotel was especially welcoming.Eating in the Hotel seems to be quite expensive - 13 euros + 7% tax per person for breakfast and a table d'ote menu in an evening for 30 euro's per person. To be fare however we never ate in the Hotel so I can't comment on the food.When you book I would try and avoid rooms 10.11  12. I could imagine these being especially noisy as they are on the first floor mezanine. The rooms to go for all in end 5 or 8. Eg 25, 38, 45 etc. Theses are the corner rooms which are bigger than the normal one's.The taxi from the airport to the Hotel is around 20 euro's.Las Ramblas is about a 20 minute walk away. At the bottom of Las Ramblas is Port Vell which is a large shopping complex. Don't miss St. Joseph food market about 1/2 way down Las Ramblas on the right. Not to be missed!Considering it is a large city we were a little disappointed at the restaurants in Barcelona. Not as much choice as we expected.The Rocafort tram stop is 2 minutes walk from the Hotel if you want to go further.A great hotel a little way out of the centre but no worse for it! 
