<Author>IvanhP
<Content>Does not deserve #4 Rank on Tripadvisor My wife and I stayed here post cruise for only one evening and I have to say, i was very disappointed.My wife and I travel a considerable amount worldwide and often use tripadvisor to aid in our decisions. We chose this hotel based on tripadvisor reviews and rankings... and they are not well deserved. We disembarked our ship early in the morning and requested an early check-in. Upon arrival I asked teh front desk if we could check in early and without even checking, they denied our request and said not til after 12 noon. So we left our bags with them and walked around Barcelona. The location of this hotel is 5-10 minutes walking from La Ramblas and Pl Catalunya and there are very few restaurants or shopping in the area. Upon our return, the hotel was unable to give us a key to our room, because heir system was down. But they did allow us to bring our bags up. The front desk attendant showed us to our room and using his master key he opened up our room and then left us w/o a key. He promised he'd see what he could do, but after 15 minutes waiting in our room, we never heard from him.The room key is NEEDED to activate the lights and power, so this didn't do us any good. That meant we had to shower in the dark and my wife could not use her hair dryer. Upon leaving i checked with the front desk when i could have a key to my room and they said it would be around 3pm. I also had to correct them before leaving... they assigned us one room and gave us a notecard with a room number on it, but they put us in a different room on the same floor. While we were gone, i didn't want them letting someone else into our room b/c of a mismatch.We left for lunch and came back later in the afternoon to get ready for dinner. While my wife was getting ready, i asked the front desk if they could give me access to the free Wi Fi. But they didn'y know how to set it ip on my Mac. In the US, my Mac just finds wireless network available, you select it, and enter the password... i guess their process was different. So unable to use my laptop, i used their computers in their business center. But all their computers were set up in Italian. I asked the front desk attendant if she could show me how to change the lanugage on the cpu, but she didn't know how to do that either. The hotel was clean and decoration was modern... but the overall experience was sub par. The showers look cool but they flood the entire bathroom floor...We were never offered any apology for our inconvenience or anything. RIDICULOUSAt $200 a night i'm sure you can find a better place to stay. 
