<Author>Popintops
<Content>Certainly one to avoid We stayed at this hotel for 4 nights. I selected it because of the good reviews on this site but I really can not believe that this is the same hotel represented by other contributors to the Trip Advisor community. My complaints are as follows:1) The air conditioning throughout the hotel had been set far too high and, despite our efforts to reduce the heat in the bedroom, it was unbearably hot. We could not open the windows because of the traffic noise from outside which was continuous even in the night. 2) This hotel is on a very busy main junction and is therefore very noisy if you are unfortunately allocated a bedroom on the main road side of the building. 3) The staff at reception were not at all helpful, pleasant or courteous and seemed to consider my requests, such as for booking taxis or directions to restaurants, to be a major inconvenience.4) Our room was never serviced adequately. On one day, our towels were removed and not replaced. We did not receive the standard toiletries per day and had one tiny little bar of soap for the entire visit. The cleaner STOLE my times newspaper that I was in the middle of reading and I was forced to retrieve it from her trolley which was parked further down the corridor.5) Of most seriousness, however, was the lack of security at this hotel. On our last day, for example, we packed most of the bags and went to breakfast. On returning to our room we then found that somebody, presumably the cleaner, had opened our room door and had left it unattended and wide open with our bags in full view of passers by along the corridor. This hotel has notices everywhere informing people to guard their belongings and yet their staff made it possible for somebody to walk off with all our bags. Also, because our flight was late in the evening, we asked to leave our bags at reception on the last day after check out to collect later. They do not have any safe place for such bag storage, as is customary at all good hotels, especially those claiming to be a 4 star rating, and our bags were just left on the floor at the side of reception. Fortunately, nothing was in fact stolen but they certainly have a security issue at this hotel and a total disrespect for their client鈥檚 property.6) The breakfasts were shambolic. It was the usual buffet style affair BUT the table of provisions was very small and not stocked or monitored adequately so every day I had to ask for basics such as plates, tea pots, spoons, bread etc.7) This hotel is a very modern style but the designers had thought little about the practicalities of their ideas e.g. the bathroom and shower looked fabulous BUT it proved impractical to actually use the shower without completely flooding the bathroom floor. Similarly, the sink area was totally impossible to use without it drenching the surrounding surfaces and it lacked an overflow outlet.It was a choice between this and the Hesperia Presidente and I wish now I had booked the latter because I have stayed at other Hesperia hotels and have never experienced any such problems. 
