<Author>exploremore10
<Content>What a find!! Hotel Emilia is located on a side street, off a main road and is a 1 minute walk away from Rocafort Metro station which makes travelling around the city a piece of cake, it takes about 5 mins. to get to La Rambla metro station and for 7.20euros you get 10 metro trips. It is a 15 minute walk from montjuic - the very impressive national art gallery with the magic fountains and quite possibly the finest view over Barcelona. The olympic stadium is located just behind montjuic. Even though this hotel is not directly in the centre of Barcelona there are some great restaurants, patisseries and cafes located near by, which are much more reasonably priced than some of the restaurants on La Rambla-one of which tried to charge us 10euros for a beer. Next door to the restaurant is a superb cafe/deli/wine shop, and a craking little authentic mexican restaurant is just around the corner.The hotel staff were very helpful, freindly and spoke excellent english. The hotel is immaculately clean with good sized rooms, queen size beds and full length windows which slide open like a patio door. The roof terrace was a real suprise when we first saw it, with sophisticated furniture providing a very relaxed atmosphere.The breakfast was lovely, with a good selection of breads, baguettes, salami, proscuitto, cheeses, cereals, drinks etc. 
