<Author>KeithRHooper
<Content>Great Location Friendly Staff The Hotel Villa Emilia is a great modernist boutique hotel. The rooms are of a good size and although the large than queen bed is two singles pushed together this did not cause a problem. The bed is a little hard for our tastes however we had no trouble sleeping in the quiet atmosphere. We liked the idea of being able to open the windows as you could let the sounds of the city in and to be able to close them to enjoy the air conditioning. The nearest railway station (Rocafort) is literally two minute walk from the front door. The Hub station Espanya is one station further up the line or ten minutes walk up the Gran Via de les Corts Catalanes. From Espanya it is possible to catch trains all over Barcelona and importantly to Montserrat (which is must). The Hotel staff was very friendly. The reception staff was very helpful and had a very good grasp of English (which was great considering my very poor Latin American Spanish) and helped us out with all manner of enquires even arranging a taxi for us on our departure. The roof top bar was hit (although a little chilly as the evening wore on), service was great via an intercom to the Zinc Bar. The breakfast bar was good an honest self serve buffet that was well serviced with no problems with food or drink running out. Over all the Hotel Villa Emilia is a very comfortable hotel that is well located away from the hurley burly with an excellent train service. Montjuic is a longish walk away, however by using the railway system (including the funicular and the cable car) a visit to the castle where there is fabulous view of the harbour and city. It is then long but leisurely stroll down hill to the old Olympic area, the National Art Museum and the Magic Fountains. There are great number of cafes and bars in the surrounding streets to keep the most adventurous happy. The attentive staff ensured that we had a no fuss seven day stay. A very good no fuss holiday with great staff in a very good location. 
